               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-81-person620">
                  EDWARD 
                  BURRIDGE
               <interp inst="t18290115-81-person620" type="surname" value="BURRIDGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-81-person620" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-81-person620" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 18th of December I was in St. John's-wood-road, and heard a cry of Stop thief! I found the prisoner and another boy charged with robbing a till of 3d., and in the prisoner's hat I found this shirt, which he said he found in the road, covered with straw; I took it to Mrs. Rich, who identified it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in the Wellington-road, and saw this shirt under a hedge; I took it up, and was going on - a boy was called after; the officer came and took me.</p>
